[A] China: National Health Commission, 83 572 total cases, 4634 deaths
Date: Tue 7 Jul 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [abridged, edited]
http://en.nhc.gov.cn/2020-07/08/c_81028.htm


On 7 Jul 2020 (as of midnight 8 Jul 2020):
- 7 new cases of confirmed infections (all were imported cases, 4 in Inner Mongolia autonomous region, 1 in Shanxi province, 1 in Guangdong province, and 1 in Yunnan province); no new cases of suspected infections and no deaths.
- A total of 1949 imported cases have been reported.
- 83 572 confirmed cases and 4634 deaths; 78 548 recovered and discharged from hospital; 765 012 close contacts with infected patients; and 4214 are under medical observation.
- 6 new asymptomatic cases (including 5 imported cases); no asymptomatic cases confirmed as symptomatic; 117 asymptomatic cases under medical observation (including 79 imported cases).
- 1299 cases in Hong Kong [an increase of 14 cases since 6 Jul 2020], 46 in Macau.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
and
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[The 7 new confirmed cases in the last 24 hours were all imported and no cases were reported from Beijing.

There were 6 newly confirmed infections in asymptomatic individuals and no new conversions from asymptomatic to symptomatic in the past 24 hours. Since 18 May 2020, there have been 36 cases of conversion from asymptomatic to symptomatic infections reported by China.

Hong Kong reported 14 new cases. According to a Centre for Health Protection press release, "the newly reported cases announced today involve 10 males and 4 females aged between 14 and 85. 5 had travel history during the incubation period." The webpage mentions a total of 1300 cases (1299 confirmed and 1 probable case). Locally acquired cases include 1 resident of a residential care home for the elderly (RCHE), the others are considered most likely community acquired, information re possible restaurants (https://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/202007/07/P2020070700833.htm).

Takeaway message: China continues to have importations of infected individuals with SARS-CoV-2, many of whom are detected as asymptomatic at the time of positive PCR testing.

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://sacu.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/provmap.png, and a HealthMap/ProMED map is available at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7551918,155. - Mod.MPP]

