Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In the past 24 hours, according to the report at the source URL, the tally of confirmed cases of COVID-19 in South Korea has increased by 63 cases with no new deaths, compared with 44 cases and 1 new death in the previous day (6 Jul 2020). The daily newly confirmed case count has been at or below 100 for 85 consecutive days. There were 30 locally transmitted cases: Gyeonggi (11), Gwangju (7), Seoul (5), Chungnam (3), Daejeon (2), Incheon (1), and Jeonnam (1), and 33 imported cases -- airport quarantine (11), Gyeonggi (7), Seoul (5), Chungnam (3), Jeonbuk (2), Gyeongnam (2), Daegu (1), Gwangju (1), and Gyeongbuk (1). There were 6 provinces reporting no newly confirmed cases (compared with 10 provinces yesterday, 6 Jul 2020).

According to data from the "ncov" website of the Ministry of Health and Welfare, the cumulative confirmation rate has been steady at 1.0% (http://ncov.mohw.go.kr/).

The overall impression hasn't changed: Lifting of measures has been accompanied by increases in locally acquired infections through increasing clusters related to gatherings of people at employment (bringing it outside employment to contacts) and in houses of worship, and bars and clubs. But, that being said, importations are also playing a major role in the country. It would be nice to know the asymptomatic rate being detected, and the proportion of asymptomatic infections detected that go on to clinical disease.

Takeaway message: Importations continue to be a challenge, and gatherings whether social or religious are key foci for enlarging clusters (unchanged from previous 4 day's message).

A map of South Korea showing provinces can be seen at https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/korea-south-administrative-map.htm and a HealthMap/ProMED map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7551918,195. - Mod.MPP]

