[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of reported cases of COVID-19 worldwide is now 11 949 280, with reports of cases by 217 countries and territories worldwide. Given the level of daily newly confirmed cases, tomorrow (8 Jul 2020) the global total of cases will cross the 12 million mark, having crossed the 11 million mark on 3 Jul 2020. The global case count rose by 1.8% in the past 24 hours. The USA, with more than 3.09 million confirmed cases, now represents 25.9% of the global cases of COVID-19, and Brazil with more than 1.67 million cases represents 14.0% of the global cases of COVID-19. Other countries such as India, Mexico, Chile, Peru, South Africa, Saudi Arabia, and Pakistan are reporting increased numbers of new and cumulative cases as well. If one tallies the total cumulative case counts for the top 5 countries (USA, Brazil, India, Russia, and Peru), they represent over half of the total cases reported globally (54.6%). A global total of 546 601 deaths have been reported, an increase of 5941 deaths in the past 24 hours.

In descending rank order, the USA is number 1 for the number of newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours, followed by Brazil, India, South Africa, Russia, Mexico, Colombia Peru, Saudi Arabia, and Bangladesh. All countries that are currently experiencing major community-based transmission and considered global hot spots. The range in the top 10 daily newly confirmed cases went from 3027 to 56 251.

Impression: The SARS-CoV-2 is still actively being transmitted in all regions of the world and many countries are showing increases in their daily newly confirmed case counts. - Mod.MPP]
